The paper discusses citation metrics and their limitations in evaluating scientific impact, which is a topic that is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. However, the focus on scholarly publications and the use of statistical methods suggest that cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely sub-category. Other possible sub-categories include cs.CY (Computational Geometry), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
